{{Quote|&hellip;a Force technique permitting [&hellip;] the projection of phantoms across space. It appears in every way to match the lost technique of Darth Vectivus.|Dician|<ref name="Fury" />}}
'''Force phantoms''', also called '''Sith phantasms''', were the product of an elaborate [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] ritual that allowed a [[darksider]] to create lifelike apparitions from the siphoned [[The Force/Legends|Force energy]] of another life form, irrespective of [[Sentience/Legends|sentience]], and project them across the expanse of the [[Realspace/Legends|cosmos]]. An [[Force power/Legends|ability]] that required considerable mental reserve and strength of will, Force phantoms manifested in the physical realm and served whatever inclinations that their creator desired. Their insidious nature was only revealed when they were destroyed, at which [[Time/Legends|time]] the being or creature to which the phantom was anchored also [[Death/Legends|perished]]. The power was developed and perfected by the [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord]] [[Darth Vectivus]], and much later&mdash;by [[40 ABY/Legends|40 ABY]]&mdash;the technique had been thought lost among modern Sith. On the contrary, the rituals for conjuring Force phantoms had been discovered and mastered by the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lady]] [[Lumiya]], and later the [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] [[Alema Rar]], both of whom brought them to bear heavily during the [[Second Galactic Civil War]]. The secret of their creation was coveted by several beings during that same time, but none so highly as the members of the mysterious [[One Sith]] Order, which, rather than allow access to such power to fall into the hands of the [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]], destroyed the former [[The Home|asteroid home]] of [[Darth/Legends|Darth]] Vectivus, which was also the [[Vergence/Legends|source]] from where the last known practitioners harnessed the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] for the creation of Force phantoms. A Force phantom was similar to the advanced Jedi technique known as [[Dopplegänger]], being that it was an astral projection of a being created through use of the Force.

==Description==
===Creation===
{{Quote|Every phantom you see here, every one you encounter, is connected to something that is distinctly real, distinctly alive&mdash;though possibly far, far away.''"<br />"''You're lying.''"<br />"''No, I'm not. You struck, and somewhere, some creature, perhaps a baby bantha, squealed in pain and was severed, killed before the disbelieving eyes of its mother&mdash;''"<br />"''Stop it.''"<br />"''Why? It's the truth. Baby banthas are quite cute, you know. A terrible shame to see one cut in half.|Darth Vectivus explains the incongruity of Force phantoms to Nelani Dinn|<ref name="Betrayal" />}}
[[File:Darthvec.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Darth Vectivus, inventor of the Force phantom technique]]
[[The Force/Legends|Force]] phantoms were the result of a complex [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] ritual that was dependent on the availability of a subject, [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] or otherwise, with sufficient mental facility and vitality to sustain the influence of the initiator. Through the Force, the [[darksider]] searched for the mentality of an unsuspecting target to serve as an anchor in reality; foreknowledge of the prey's whereabouts served to expedite the process, but was not required. The target aura was perceived in [[Color/Legends|color]] and distinct from that of the originator's, whose own influence surrounded the victim in bright sparks of Force energy. Once securely affixed to the initial subject, the creator withdrew his or her influence and sought out another pliant mentality capable of also withstanding their prolonged assertion. The range of possibilities manifested in a variety of hues, and only through close scrutiny of each was an optimal host discovered. [[Species/Legends|Species]], [[Gender/Legends|gender]], physical health, and current cognitive state were all ascertainable through the inspection, and each lent weight toward the eventual selection. The creator ultimately attached himself or herself to this mind and began to drain life energy in a manner akin to that of a spectral [[Parasite/Legends|parasite]]. The extracted essence was then given corporeal form and shaped into whatever likeness the creator desired, to travel wherever in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] the conjurer chose. [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitives]] who concentrated saw a phantom's arrival fill their vision, while beings who had not expected one's presence were startled by the sudden appearance.<ref name="Exile" /><ref name="Fury" /> Those not attuned to the Force witnessed a shimmering form develop right before their [[Eye/Legends|eyes]].<ref name="Betrayal" />

===Drawbacks===
{{Quote|Coordinating the actions of several Force phantoms at once? Very tiring. Try it sometime.|Lumiya, exhausted by the control of multiple, simultaneous Force phantoms|<ref name="Betrayal" />}}
While an effective<ref name="Betrayal" /> and convenient ability, the mere ritualistic preparation of Force phantoms was an extremely exhausting process. The harvested life essence could do nothing to replenish the reserves of the darksider, and, without sufficient rest, the conjurer was beset with fatigue. Greater distance made the procedure additionally taxing, and prolonged long-range projection riddled the body with tremors as the creator struggled to maintain concentration. Because of the depleting nature of the technique, copious reserves of Force energy were required, usually those found in [[Vergence/Legends|reservoirs]] of [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side power]].<ref name="Exile" /> The inexperienced were compelled to [[Sleep/Legends|sleep]] for days at a [[Time/Legends|time]] as they built up the necessary tolerance to its effects.<ref name="Fury" /> If interrupted, the projection wavered as would a piece of fabric in a breeze; if focus was totally broken, or the creator was overextended, the [[Mind trick/Legends#Force illusion|illusion]] disappeared.<ref name="Exile" /> Phantoms were restricted to the [[Gravity/Legends|gravitational]] standards of the [[Planet/Legends|world]] where the host was located<ref name="Betrayal" /> and were unable to fight with ranged weapons, instead forced to make do with the limits of their physical [[Limb/Legends|extensions]].<ref name="Fury" />

Various [[Sensor/Legends|sensor]] applications were able to expose a Force phantom's duplicity; through preliminary examination, the apparitions radiated with considerably more haziness than actual flesh and [[Blood/Legends|blood]]. [[Infrared/Legends|Infrared]] scrutiny revealed a monotonously consistent hue, much different from the spectrum of color emanated by living beings. Both radar and sonar pings revealed their nonexistence, as Force phantoms had no real mass to reflect the signals. Force-trained individuals saw not only what was projected, but also the life to which the phantom was attached.<ref name="Fury" />

==Applications==
{{Quote|Hello, dear. You realize you're dead.''"<br />"''Of course I'm dead. I've been dead for years. But it doesn't mean I don't exist.''"<br />"''Well, that's the point, isn't it? The doctors all say that you don't, that your very existence rests only in my mind. But they say I'm getting better.''"<br />"''I don't exist just in your mind. I exist in fact. Phantoms of the mind can't open a door and free you, can they?|Admiral Matric Klauskin and a Force phantom of his wife, conjured by Lumiya|<ref name="Exile" />}}
From [[Spy/Legends|espionage]]<ref name="Exile" /> to harassment of the enemy<ref name="Fury" /> and even simple communication, Force phantoms were a practical means to a variety of ends. Conjurers frequently appeared as themselves, with full access to their breadth of [[Force power/Legends|Force abilities]] and [[Lightsaber combat/Legends|lightsaber skill]]<ref name="Betrayal" /> and fully capable of inflicting harm.<ref name="Fury" /> They usually materialized in their true form,<ref name="Exile" /> at times physically-enhanced<ref name="Fury" /> or not in their particular likeness at all. Darksiders commonly attacked their foes by projecting multiple simultaneous phantoms, such as swarms of creatures like [[Mynock/Legends|mynocks]], forcing the quarry to divide their attention while also defending themselves.<ref name="Betrayal" /><ref name="Fury" /> Those followers of the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] way who were unfamiliar with the phenomena mistook phantoms for [[Force ghost/Legends|Force ghosts]].<ref name="Exile" /> When their true nature was revealed, Jedi were especially confounded, given the potential innocence of the beings to whom each apparition was attached; damage suffered by the phantom was in turn transferred to the life it was anchored to.<ref name="Betrayal" /><ref name="Fury" /> Manifestations of loved ones also worked to bewilder the creator's adversaries<ref name="Betrayal" /> and challenged the sanity of non-Force-sensitives, who rationalized the occurrences as ghost sightings or close encounters with "phantoms of the mind."<ref name="Exile" />

==Users==
{{Quote|Even as I speak, I am unaware of myself. Of thinking, of decision making. Could I, in fact, be nothing?''"<br />"''No, I can feel you. Gleaming in the Force. Shining with the dark side.''"<br />"''That's not me. That's whomever I am connected to.|[[Darth Vectivus]] reveals his nature as a Force phantom to [[Nelani Dinn]]|<ref name="Betrayal" />}}
[[File:LumiyaKinooineHeadshot.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Lumiya learned and mastered the creation of Force phantoms.]]
The Force phantom technique was invented by [[Darth Vectivus]],<ref name="DVCSWE">{{CSWECite|III|298|Vectivus, Darth}}</ref> a [[Sith Master/Legends|Sith Master]] whose lair was a palatial [[The Home|asteroid abode]] situated over a nexus of dark side energy.<ref name="Fury" /> Vectivus perfected the technique and even retained the ability after his [[Death/Legends|death]],<ref name="DVCSWE" /> but widespread knowledge of the ritual was believed by succeeding Sith to have been lost over the centuries.<ref name="Fury" /> By [[40 ABY/Legends|40 ABY]], current [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lady of the Sith]] [[Lumiya]], who had since taken up residence in Vectivus' former habitat,<ref name="Betrayal" /> encountered the spirit of the deceased [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] and learned his ancient power.<ref name="DVCSWE" /> With it, she relentlessly tormented [[Galactic Alliance Defense Fleet]] [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Matric Klauskin]] by appearing as his late [[Marriage/Legends|wife]] [[Edela Klauskin|Edela]]. Lacking Force sensitivity or the technological means to discern the truth, Klauskin was driven insane.<ref name="Exile" /> As the [[Galaxy/Legends|galaxy]] descended into instability, Lumiya utilized her ability to distress her long-time enemies, [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Masters]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke]] and [[Mara Jade Skywalker]], with simultaneous apparitions of their [[Darth Caedus|nephew]] and [[Ben Skywalker|son]], who also fought phantoms of their uncle and mother, respectively.<ref name="Betrayal" /> Shortly afterward, young Skywalker and [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Nelani Dinn]] were beleaguered by a multitude of mynock phantoms in the bowels of the [[Asteroid/Legends|asteroid]], all conjured by Lumiya.<ref name="NDCSWE">{{CSWECite|I|190|Dinn, Nelani}}</ref> A separate phantom of [[Darth/Legends|Darth]] Vectivus himself then appeared only to Dinn with ominous warnings. Lumiya, meanwhile, created a Force phantom of Darth Caedus, the Sith [[Lord/Legends|Lord]] whom Jacen Solo would become, as she attempted to seduce him to the dark side.<ref name="Betrayal" /> The Dark Lady later appeared to Solo on the planet [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], after she had suffered crippling wounds in [[Duel on Roqoo Depot|combat]] with [[Grand Master/Legends|Grand Master]] Skywalker. Her injuries caused visible strain, but Lumiya's tremendous strength of will allowed her to perform the ritual successfully. Solo recognized and marveled at the practicality of the ability and desired to learn it for himself. As the [[Second Galactic Civil War]] progressed, Lumiya continued her phantasmal manipulation of Admiral Klauskin, who eventually retired from active military service.<ref name="Exile" />

Following Lumiya's [[Duel on Terephon|death]] on the [[Hapan]] world of [[Terephon]],<ref name="Sacrifice">''[[Legacy of the Force: Sacrifice]]''</ref> her asteroid home was appropriated by the [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] [[Alema Rar]],<ref name="Inferno">''[[Legacy of the Force: Inferno]]''</ref> who, with much practice and study of notes left behind by the Dark Lady, became a consummate wielder of the Force phantom ability. Rar likened herself to a [[Deity/Legends|goddess]] as she occupied the uppermost chamber of the habitat and infused herself with enough of the asteroid's pooled darkness to create an infinite number and variety of Force phantoms. The insane [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] preferred to display a revitalized body, one she considered beautiful and eternal, that was conspicuously without the farrago of deformities that had since become her most recognized appearance. Her projections also included flocks of giant mynocks, which she used to endlessly badger various members of the [[Solo family/Legends|Solo family]]. Members of the [[One Sith]] Order secluded on the planet [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]], who had been under the impression that Vectivus' technique was lost to history, became remarkably interested in its resurfacing. When they learned that Rar was the current master of the ability, one of their number, the Sith Lord [[Dician]] was ordered to annex the asteroid habitat and take the Twi'lek into custody so that the Korriban Sith might extract the secrets of Force phantom creation from her. Dician, however, made her superiors aware of the Jedi's interest in Rar as well as their imminent convergence upon the asteroid, and the mission changed from one of capture to one of destruction. From her [[Flagship/Legends|flagship]], the [[Poison Moon (starship)|''Poison Moon'']], Dician obliterated the asteroid with [[fission bomb]]s, just after the departure of a [[Alema Rar Task Force|Jedi strike team]] that had [[Skirmish at The Home|infiltrated]] the asteroid and [[Assassin/Legends|assassinated]] Rar. With the Dark Jedi's death and the asteroid's destruction, the secrets of Force phantom creation were effectively eradicated.<ref name="Fury" />

==Behind the scenes==
Force phantoms first appeared in ''[[Legacy of the Force: Betrayal]]'', the introductory novel in the nine-part ''[[Star Wars: Legacy of the Force]]'' series. It went on to feature as the primary means of Force harassment employed by the series' main dark side&ndash;wielding antagonists in ''[[Legacy of the Force: Exile]]'' and ''[[Legacy of the Force: Fury]]''. The ability was ambiguously mentioned in ''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]''{{'s}} entry for Darth Vectivus and received a specific reference in ''[[Fate of the Jedi: Omen]]'', the second book in the ''Legacy of the Force''&ndash;succeeding, nine-part [[Star Wars: Fate of the Jedi|''Fate of the Jedi'']] series.

